Quote:
The Headcharger engine has been filled up again and they're coming to deliver their 3rd album "the end starts here" like an old run-down Mustang still mile thirsty.
But what is running the roaring Headcharger machine? An explosive mixture of Metal and Rock n' Roll.
In the trunk you'll find their two previous albums released in 2005 (Headcharger) and 2007 (Watch the Sun).
At the wheel : 5 guys from Normandy who like to put the pedal to the floor like Every time I Die (The invention of solitude) as much as the Lynyrd Skynyrd southern rock vibes (Harvey Keitel's syndrome).
And if that high-powered racing car switches to a dark lament that Alice In Chains wouldn't disown(The end starts here), it's only to take off like a shot while a lively harmonica tune is coming out from their open windows (Would you?).
With 300 shows behind them, Headcharger is charging French cities to perform shows as tuned as a stunning V8 with a rhythm section that has been given too much fuel, guitars full of bite and vocals both steady and rough.
